                         <note>The scribe rarely has to complete a line of text on another line. The challenge is addressed mainly through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., ff. 7r, 26r, etc.).</note>
                         <add>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (ff. 10r, 76v, 85r, 90r, 91r, 95v, 115v, 116v, 118r, etc.); and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (ff. 99v and 142r); and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (f. 136v, line 6).</add>
